parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause a range of issues, including engine stalling, rough idling, and short circuits, which can lead to fires, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: faulty horn and passenger window operation
and a strong smell of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of engine wiring insulation can cause shorts in the engine wiring, leading to poor engine performance, stalling, and potentially even engine fires, which can pose a significant risk to vehicle safety and occupants.
symptoms: burning smell or signs of burning at the site of the failure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty air mass flow sensor can cause the engine light to come on, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially even engine stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vacuum Hose Failure (A/C and EGR Systems)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked or broken vacuum hoses can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to decreased cooling performance, and can also affect the exhaust gas recirculation (EGR) system, potentially increasing emissions and decreasing engine performance.
A faulty wire to the A/C relay can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to decreased cooling performance, and potentially even electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Diesel Engine Preglow Wire Harness Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the diesel engine preglow wire harness can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the engine cranks but does not start
the engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle experiences a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS braking system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the vehicle experiences unusual or spongy brake pedal feel
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the vehicle experiences a loss of traction or stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The traction control warning light is illuminated
the vehicle experiences unusual or reduced traction
the vehicle wheels spin or lose grip
the vehicle experiences a loss of stability or control.
